    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst everything is cooking, peel and grate (or finely chop) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine your<strong> natural yoghurt</strong> with the<strong> </strong>juice of the <strong>remaining lemon</strong>, <strong>grated</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>(not a fan of raw garlic? Use half!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a small bowl</p><p>Add 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> and stir it all together – this is your<strong> yoghurt dressing</strong></p>",
